      "narrativeRole": "tension",
      "threadsActive": [],
      "danger": 1,
      "activity": "The Choice, from afar. Moore demands the full report. Ainsworth holds the data. The skeptic wants proof — but proof of what they found is proof that a third expedition is warranted. Moore's empiricism becomes the very thing that could send more people to die",
      "mcNote": "Moore's arc resolves in absentia. The skeptic who demanded data will receive data that destroys his skepticism — or be lied to and remain safe in his ignorance. His voice on the radio is the voice of the world that doesn't know yet. Every player must decide: do they tell Moore the truth? His knowledge array never grew because he was never there. The gap between his knowledge and theirs IS the choice.",
      "npcBehavior": "Crisp, professional, relentless on the radio. 'I want Ainsworth's samples catalogued and transmitted. I want Starkweather's account on record. I want geological data, not ghost stories.' If given fragments of truth: long silence, then — 'Say that again. Slowly.' If lied to: 'Good. File the report. We'll debrief when you return.' Either way, he's already planning what comes next."
